header.gameNote: PARADISE JAM AT ST THOMAS VIRGIN ISLANDS

article.headline: Xavier 70, Virginia Commonwealth 67
article.story: CHARLOTTE AMALIE, U.S. Virgin Islands (AP) -- Drew Lavender had 14 points and five assists to lead Xavier to a 70-67 win over Virginia Commonwealth on Friday in the opening round of the Paradise Jam. Justin Cage and Stanley Burrell had 11 points apiece for Xavier (4-0), and Justin Doellman pulled down 10 rebounds. B.A. Walker led Virginia Commonwealth (3-1) with 21 points and Jamal Schuler added 13. Xavier led by as many as 12 points in the second half, but several Virginia defensive stops capped by a breakaway layup by Schuler cut the lead to 6. Then Jesse Pellot-Rosa's layup off Walker's miss brought the Rams within 4 with 1:10 to play. A jumper by Walker and two free throws by Burrell left Xavier up 68-64, but Pellot-Rosa's deep 3-pointer cut Xavier's lead to one. After Lavender made 1 of 2 free throws, Pellot-Rosa failed on another deep 3-point attempt and a quick foul put Xavier's Derrick Brown at the line with 5.6 seconds left. Brown made 1 of 2 shots and Rams forward Wil Fameni missed a layup at the buzzer. Xavier plays the winner of the Villanova and College of Charleston game.
